        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 31 at 7:29AM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 729 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Aliceville to near Alamucha. Movement was
east at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Aliceville, Dillburg, New Mount Hebron, Belmont, Panola, Sumterville,
Eutaw Municipal Airport, George Downer Airport, West Greene,
McDowell, Thornhill, Bellamy, Pleasant Ridge, Lewiston, Benevola,
Johnston Lake, Epes, Birdine, Memphis, and Gainesville Lake
Campground.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until noon CDT for
southwestern and west central Alabama.</instruction>
